Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%mins}.
Turn halfway through.

While the wedges cook, halve, peel and slice the @red onion{1/2}(sliced as thinly
as you can).

Pop it into a #small bowl{} and add the @red wine vinegar{12%grams} and the
@sugar{1%tsp} for the pickle. Add a @?salt{pinch}, mix together and set aside
to pickle.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

> TIP: Keep the other half of the red onion for another recipe.

In a #large bowl{}, combine the garlic, @lemon & herb seasoning{1%sachet},
@panko breadcrumbs{10%grams} and the @salt{1/4%tsp} and @water{2%tbsp} for the
breadcrumbs, then add the @British beef mince{240%grams}.

Season with pepper and mix together with your hands. Roll into even-sized
balls, then shape into 1cm thick burgers, 1 per person.

> TIP: The burgers will shrink a little during cooking.
> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the burgers onto a baking tray. Bake on the middle shelf until cooked
through, ~{12-15%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When the burgers and wedges are nearly ready, halve the @burger buns{2}.
Pop them onto a baking tray and into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%mins}.

Strain the liquid from the pickled onion into a #medium bowl{}. Add the
@wild rocket{20%grams} to the bowl and toss to coat in the pickling liquid.
Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

When everything's ready, spread the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} over the bun bases.
Top the bases with the beef burgers and the pickled onion, then crumble the
@Greek style salad cheese{50%grams} on top. Sandwich shut with the bun lids.

Serve with the wedges and rocket salad alongside. Enjoy!